{"id":"316849639_Multiple_Facets_for_Dynamic_Information_Flow_with_Exceptions","abstract":"JavaScript is the source of many security problems, including cross-site scripting attacks and malicious advertising code. Central to these problems is the fact that code from untrusted sources runs with full privileges. Information flow controls help prevent violations of data confidentiality and integrity.\nThis article explores faceted values, a mechanism for providing information flow security in a dynamic manner that avoids the stuck executions of some prior approaches, such as the no-sensitive-upgrade technique. Faceted values simultaneously simulate multiple executions for different security levels to guarantee termination-insensitive noninterference. We also explore the interaction of faceted values with exceptions, declassification, and clearance.","authors":["Thomas H. Austin","Tommy Schmitz","Cormac Flanagan"],"meta":["May 2017ACM Transactions on Programming Languages and Systems 39(3):1-56","DOI:10.1145/3024086"],"references":["276994246_Value-Sensitive_Hybrid_Information_Flow_Control_for_a_JavaScript-Like_Language","254008327_Limiting_information_leakage_in_event-based_communication","254004635_Information_flow_analysis_for_javascript","228674170_Permissive_dynamic_information_flow_analysis","225131340_Flow-sensitive_context-sensitive_and_object-sensitive_information_flow_control_based_on_program_dependence_graphs","224361690_Preventing_Information_Leaks_through_Shadow_Executions","221668983_Rozzle_De-Cloaking_Internet_Malware","221632067_Termination-Insensitive_Noninterference_Leaks_More_Than_Just_a_Bit","221609722_An_Empirical_Study_of_Privacy-Violating_Information_Flows_in_JavaScript_Web_Applications","221609481_Reactive_Noninterference","221608970_Security_policies_for_downgrading","221053178_Automata-Based_Confidentiality_Monitoring","221046675_Analyzing_Information_Flow_in_JavaScript-Based_Browser_Extensions","220997429_Multiple_Facets_for_Dynamic_Informatio